skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:133:4. Build a dependency DAG and remove cycles before drafting. Ensure the graph is topologically sortable for execution order.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:135:6. Write each task and child task as concrete implementation instructions.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:138:   - Existing plan update: preserve truthful terminal states (`completed`, `cancelled`) unless explicitly changed, and preserve any `**Assignee:**` / `> **Result:**` blocks that the runtime has written.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:139:8. Run the validation checklist before returning output.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:140:9. **Final scan:** re-read every `### Task`, `#### Task`, `##### Task`, or `###### Task` heading (or other declared kinds) in the output and confirm each is immediately followed by a `**State:**` line. If any task is missing `**State:**`, fix it before returning the plan. This is the most common defect — always perform this check last.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:146:- Use one H1 and match `# Rhei: <title>` (Single-File Plan) or `index.rhei.md` (Directory Workspace).
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:147:- If present, place `**States:** <state-machine-name>` as the first non-empty line after the H1, before any frontmatter or H2 section.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:148:- If present, place YAML frontmatter between the `**States:**` line and the first H2 section.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:149:- Keep `## Tasks` present and last in Single-File Plans; omit it entirely from `index.rhei.md` in Directory Workspaces.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:151:- Format every child task node as `#### <Kind> <parent>.<child>: <title>` (and deeper levels at H5/H6 when `structure.maxLevels` permits).
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:152:- Include `**State:**` on every task (root or child) with an allowed value from the resolved profile.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:153:- Place `**Prior:**` only after `**State:**` when present.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:154:- Do not author `**Assignee:**` or `> **Result:**` — these are runtime-owned.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:155:- Reference only existing tasks in each `**Prior:**` line. In a Directory Workspace, references resolve across the merged workspace graph.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:156:- Keep dependencies acyclic. A task must not self-reference and must not list its parent or any ancestor as `**Prior:**`. When follow-up work must wait for a parent task to complete, author it as a top-level sibling instead of a child.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:158:- Each child id extends its parent id by exactly one segment; sibling ids under the same parent are unique.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:159:- Ensure each task has child tasks unless the task is clearly simple and non-decomposable.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:160:- Emit no metadata fields beyond `**State:**` and `**Prior:**`.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:161:- Heading depth must not exceed the plan's `structure.maxLevels` (default `2`, maximum `4`).
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:162:- If mixed kinds are used, every heading keyword appears in `structure.nodeKinds`; `rhei` never appears there.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:164:When the CLI is available, run `rhei validate <plan>` after writing — it performs the full grammar, state, dependency, link, and terminal-coherence checks the checklist only approximates.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:168:Save Rhei Plan documents with the `.rhei.md` extension, or `.md` when the context is clear. The Directory Workspace root file is always `index.rhei.md`.
skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:174:1. Preserve unchanged sections, task IDs, frontmatter, `**Assignee:**` lines, and `> **Result:**` blocks.
